Quote:  Bush drain: the next cheapest alternative. Dig the trench at least 900 mm deep. Put in a 600mm layer of branches with fine leaves and twigs at the top to stop soil filtering down into the bigger wood. If you have a cheap metal
Source, use about 450mm of scrub then 150 mm of coarse shingle.
